  -- term by term via `affineBaseChange_pushforward_iso`.  Flatness of `A ‚Üí B`
  -- makes `- ‚äó_A B` exact, so it commutes with `H‚Å∞`, giving the isomorphism
  -- `H‚Å∞(X, F) ‚äó_A B ‚âÖ H‚Å∞(X_B, F_B)`.  Needs the (missing) ƒåech-cohomology /
